title: When the King Came: Stories from the Four Gospels
creator: George Hodges
description: LibriVox recording of When the King Came, by George Hodges. Read by Laura Caldwell THIS tells how once the King of Glory came from heaven to visit us here on earth and live amongst us; how He was born in Bethlehem and brought up in Nazareth; how He went about telling people of the Heavenly Kingdom, and doing good, ministering to the sick and the poor; how He was misunderstood, and disliked, and even hated, till at last they took Him in Jerusalem and nailed Him to a cross so that He died; and how, after that, He came to life again, and went back into heaven, promising to return. (Summary from the Preface of When the King Came) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
